---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Story"
  description="How EduMyna emerged from real education constraints, systems failures, and a decade of operating programs at scale."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-4xl py-20">
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight">
          A platform shaped by reality
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-600 max-w-3xl">
          EduMyna wasn’t imagined in a pitch deck. It emerged slowly from the
          operational realities of running education programs where scale,
          quality, and accountability actually mattered.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <Container>
    <!-- Video -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto my-20">
      <div class="aspect-video rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-100 flex items-center justify-center text-slate-500">
        Founder video goes here
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-3 text-center">
        A short, direct explanation of why EduMyna exists
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Timeline -->
    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-32">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-12">
        The evolution
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Card -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6">
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-400 font-medium">2013</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-2">
            Entering education through operations
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            The work began inside a nonprofit education ecosystem struggling with
            scale and sustainability. The real problem wasn’t content. It was
            systems.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6">
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-400 font-medium">Early years</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-2">
            Online-first became unavoidable
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            Programs had to work across geographies and maturity levels. This
            forced an online-first approach long before it became mainstream.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6">
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-400 font-medium">Iteration</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-2">
            The platform followed the pain
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            Every feature emerged from operational bottlenecks. Structure,
            feedback loops, and progression were built to support delivery, not
            vanity metrics.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6">
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-400 font-medium">Open source</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-2">
            Transparency over control
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
            The core was made open-source to allow adaptation, scrutiny, and long
            term trust. Self-hosting was a principle, not an upsell.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-2 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-6 bg-slate-50">
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-400 font-medium">Today</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-2">
            EduMyna
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 max-w-3xl">
            EduMyna is the consolidation of these learnings into a platform for
            people running real programs. It optimizes for clarity, iteration,
            and responsibility rather than growth-at-any-cost.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Container>
</Layout>